Tylenol 650 mg p.o. q .4 h. p . r . n . 2. Amiodarone 200 mg p.o. daily . 3. Enteric - coated aspirin 81 mg p.o. daily . 4. Dulcolax 10 mg PR every other day . 5. Colace 100 mg p.o. b . i . d . 6. Folate 1 mg p.o. daily . 7. Haldol 0.25 mg p.o. b.i.d. p . r . n . This medication should be used sparingly as the patient gets oversedated easily . Do not give over Haldol 0.25 mg at one time . 8. Insulin regular sliding scale subcutaneous a.c. and at bedtime . 9. Lactulose 30 mL p.o. q.i.d. p.r.n. for constipation . 10. Protonix 40 mg p.o. daily . 11 . Synthroid 25 mcg p.o. daily . 12. Lisinopril 10 mg p.o. daily . 13. Metamucil sugar free one packet p.o. daily . 14. Simvastatin 80 mg p.o. at bedtime . 15. Toprol XL 100 mg p.o. b.i.d. hold if systolic blood pressure less than 100 , heart rate less than 55 . 16 . Diltiazem extended release 360 mg p . o . daily , hold if systolic blood pressure less than 100 , heart rate less than 55 . 17. Plavix 75 mg p . o . daily , this medication should not be held for any reason . 18. Maalox chewable 1 - 2 tablets p.o. q .6 h. p . r . n . DISPOSITION : Upon discharge , the patient will be transported to the Ardsdo Crestver Nai Memorial Health Centers where he will continue physical therapy , occupational therapy , as well as continued medication titration . Upon discharge , the patient is in stable condition tolerating p . o . intake well . He was ambulating with minimal assistance . FOLLOW - UP APPOINTMENT : The patient has follow - up appointment scheduled with Dr. Seltz on 9 / 10 / 05 at 8 : 50 a.m. He has follow up with Dr. Okuda , his Internal Medicine physician , on 7 / 9 / 05 at 9 : 00 . In addition , he will follow up with Dr. Ionescu on 4 / 4 / 05 at 9 : 30 a . m . TO DO : Includes : 1 . The patient should have his INR checked everyday . The Coumadin was initiated at 1 mg p . o . daily on 7 / 18 / 05 . The dosage may need to be titrated in order to keep an INR between a goal of 2 - 3 . 2 . The patient should be continued on an aggressive bowel regimen to avoid constipation . 3 . The patient should have daily weights checked , he may require additional diuresis if he shows symptoms of volume overload including an increase in greater than 2 pounds weight gain in one day or 5 pounds weight gain in a week or shows symptoms of volume overload such as respiratory distress or increasing lower extremity edema . 4 .
